@NODE "overview" "Overview"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

iff2aiff reads common Amiga and generic IFF audio forms, decodes to PCM, and writes a standard AIFF or AIFC file. Sample rate, channel count, and duration follow the source. Output word size is 8-bit when the source decodes as 8-bit, otherwise 16-bit.

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Usage Information" LINK "usage"}

Key Features:
? Input: 8SVX, 16SV, AIFF, AIFC, MAUD, and other forms supported by IFFSound.lib
? Output: FORM AIFF or FORM AIFC with uncompressed PCM (NONE compression in AIFC path)
? Optional AIFC container via AIFC or COMPRESS switch
? FORCE and QUIET switches for scripting
? Non-quiet mode prints source form, rate, channels, bit depth, frame count, and output size

The tool uses the IFFSound library, modelled on iffparse.library usage, for IFF stream handling and decoding.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage" "Usage"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

iff2aiff is a command-line tool that converts IFF sound files to AIFF or AIFC.

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Command Line Options" LINK "options"}

Basic Syntax:
iff2aiff SOURCE TARGET [OPTIONS]

Required Arguments:
? SOURCE - Input IFF audio file (required)
? TARGET - Output AIFF or AIFC file (required)

Optional Switches:
? FORCE - Overwrite existing output file without prompting
? QUIET - Suppress normal output messages (errors still displayed)
? AIFC or COMPRESS - Write AIFC (FORM AIFC) instead of classic AIFF (FORM AIFF)

Note: File extension is not used to detect format. The IFF structure determines the form type.

Examples:
iff2aiff sample.8svx ram:out.aiff
iff2aiff music.maud ram:music.aiff FORCE
iff2aiff clip.aiff ram:rewrap.aifc AIFC
iff2aiff voice.iff ram:out.aiff QUIET

Output:
When not in quiet mode, iff2aiff displays:
? Command line echo
? Source FORM name (8SVX, 16SV, AIFF, AIFC, MAUD, etc.)
? Source sample rate, channel count, and bit depth
? Target format (AIFF vs AIFC) and profile (rate, channels, bit depth)
? Frame count and PCM byte size
? Output file size after write
@ENDNODE

@NODE "options" "Command Line Options"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

Detailed explanation of command-line options for iff2aiff.

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Usage Information" LINK "usage"}

FORCE:
Overwrites an existing target file without prompting. Without FORCE, iff2aiff refuses to overwrite.

Example:
iff2aiff source.8svx ram:out.aiff FORCE

QUIET:
Suppresses normal progress text. Errors still print.

Example:
iff2aiff source.8svx ram:out.aiff QUIET

AIFC or COMPRESS:
Writes FORM AIFC with uncompressed PCM instead of FORM AIFF. The ReadArgs template names the keyword COMPRESS=AIFC; either AIFC or COMPRESS may be used on the command line.

Example:
iff2aiff source.maud ram:out.aifc AIFC
@ENDNODE

@NODE "formats" "Supported IFF Sound Formats"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

iff2aiff relies on IFFSound.lib for parsing and decoding. Supported inputs include the common Amiga and interchange forms below; unsupported or corrupt files fail with an error string from IFFSoundErrorString().

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"AIFF Output" LINK "aiff"}

8SVX (8-Bit Sampled Voice):
Classic Amiga mono (typically) 8-bit sampled voice under FORM 8SVX; Fibonacci and other compressions are decoded where implemented.

16SV:
16-bit sampled voice form.

AIFF / AIFC (as input):
Existing Apple AIFF or AIFC files can be read and re-written as your chosen output container (AIFF vs AIFC) and normalized PCM layout.

MAUD (Amiga Musical Data):
Musical/sampler IFF form; decoded when supported by the library.

For chunk layouts, compression types, and AIFF/AIFC specifications, see the companion guide "IFF Sound Formats.guide" in this directory.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "aiff" "AIFF and AIFC Output"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

iff2aiff writes standard big-endian PCM suitable for most audio tools and DAWs.

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Supported Formats" LINK "formats"}

AIFF (default):
? FORM AIFF with COMM and SSND chunks
? COMM: channel count, frame count, bit depth, sample rate (80-bit IEEE extended, big-endian)
? SSND: offset and block size fields then contiguous PCM samples (layout matches AIFFEncoder_Write / decoder output)

AIFC (with AIFC or COMPRESS):
? FORM AIFC; COMM includes compression ID NONE and name "None" for uncompressed PCM

Profile:
? Sample rate, channel count, and frame count match the decoded source
? Bit depth: 8 if source decodes to 8-bit, otherwise 16

The encoder module (aiff_encoder) writes the file via DOS; no libpng or zlib is used.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "examples" "Examples"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Usage Information" LINK "usage"}

Basic conversion:
iff2aiff sys:classes/datatypes/8svx.datatype ram:test.aiff

Overwrite existing file:
iff2aiff sample.8svx ram:sample.aiff FORCE

Quiet batch:
iff2aiff a.maud ram:a.aiff QUIET
iff2aiff b.maud ram:b.aiff QUIET

AIFC output:
iff2aiff recording.aiff ram:recording.aifc COMPRESS
@ENDNODE

@NODE "troubleshooting" "Troubleshooting"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Usage Information" LINK "usage"}

Invalid or unsupported IFF:
? Confirm the file is IFF audio (not ILBM picture data)
? Check the error text after IFFSoundErrorString()
? Try a known-good 8SVX or MAUD sample

Decode errors:
? Source may use an unsupported compression or corrupt BODY
? Verify file is complete

Output file exists:
? Use FORCE to overwrite, or choose a new target name

Cannot open iffparse.library:
? Install AmigaOS iffparse.library in LIBS:

Directory instead of file:
? iff2aiff requires a file path for SOURCE and TARGET, not a volume/drawer alone
@ENDNODE

@NODE "technical" "Technical Details"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Library API" LINK "api"}

Implementation:
? iffparse.library for IFF stream parsing (PropChunk / collection pattern via IFFSound)
? IFFSound.lib for AllocIFFSound, ParseIFFSound, AnalyzeFormat, DecodeTo8Bit / DecodeTo16Bit
? aiff_encoder.c for AIFF/AIFC file layout and SSND payload
@ENDNODE

@NODE "api" "IFFSound Library API"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

IFFSound.lib provides IFF sound handling parallel to IFFPicture.lib for images.

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Technical Details" LINK "technical"}

Typical sequence (see iffsound.h and SDK/doc/iffsound.doc):
? AllocIFFSound() / FreeIFFSound()
? InitIFFSoundasDOS(), set iff_Stream, OpenIFFSound(), ParseIFFSound()
? AnalyzeFormat()
? GetSampleRate(), GetChannels(), GetSampleCount(), GetBitDepth()
? DecodeTo8Bit() or DecodeTo16Bit()

Full API documentation: SDK/doc/iffsound.doc

Related: iff2png and IFFPicture.lib (SDK/doc/iffpicture.doc, iff2png.guide).
@ENDNODE

@NODE "development" "Development"
Convert IFF audio to AIFF or AIFC format

@{"Main Index" LINK "main"}
@{"Library API" LINK "api"}

Building:
? Build IFFSound.lib from Source/iffsoundlib/ first (see BUILD.md)
? Build iff2aiff from Source/ (SMakefile target iff2aiff)
? SAS/C, SMakefile, SCOPTIONS
? At run time iff2aiff OpenLibrary("iffparse.library") � install iffparse.library in LIBS:

No zlib or libpng build step for iff2aiff.
@ENDNODE

